args.file_text:
import os
import mss
import time
from datetime import datetime

SCREENSHOTS_DIR = "screenshots"
INTERVAL_SECONDS = 5

def capture_screenshots():
    os.makedirs(SCREENSHOTS_DIR, exist_ok=True)
    with mss.mss() as sct:
        try:
            while True:
                timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")
                filename = os.path.join(SCREENSHOTS_DIR, f"screenshot_{timestamp}.png")
                sct.shot(output=filename)
                time.sleep(INTERVAL_SECONDS)
        except KeyboardInterrupt:
            print("Stopping screenshot capture.")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    capture_screenshots()

pkill Xvfb; pkill -f feedback_capture.py

# Start fresh virtual display
Xvfb :99 -screen 0 1024x768x24 &> /dev/null &

# Run capture with absolute paths and display
export DISPLAY=:99 \
&& python3 /workspace/feedback_capture.py > /workspace/capture.log 2>&1 &

# Check results after 10 seconds
sleep 10 \
&& ls -l /workspace/screenshots/ \
&& cat /workspace/capture.log"}
function.name: execute_bash
